The paper deals with compressed sensing and structured signal models, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The specific structured signal model studied in the paper - local sparsity in levels - has applications in compressive imaging (cs.CE), multi-sensor acquisition systems (cs.MM), and sparse regularization in inverse problems (cs.CV). Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely candidates.
